  "prompt": "IRMA ANAND cutoff?",
  "response": "The cutoff scores for IRMA (Institute of Rural Management Anand) can vary annually based on numerous factors including the number of applicants, the difficulty of the exam, and the specific program for which you are applying. Typically, IRMA has its own entrance exam known as the IRMA Entrance Test (IRMAT) for its programs in rural management.\n\nTo get the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding cutoff scores, it is best to check IRMA's official website or contact their admissions office directly, as they will provide the most current details on the entrance exam, including the cutoff for the specific cohort you are interested in.",
